values:
To all the fans-

Well, as Caboose stated on the post before this, we moved to www.alter-ability.airsoftcore.com. But now the entire story is updated by me, and broken into about 28 episodes, fully titled, organized, and some-what edited, which we are currently continuing. Please, for those joining in season two, please read season one so you get a general idea of what's going on and how you want to design your character. If you like what you see, refer us to friends! We love our fans and we hope you all love us as well- if you have any questions, comments, concerns, let us know on the site listed above!

Easy steps- type in the site above, go to the left side panel, click on the forums link, then alter-ability, then "yeah, about this"- all the posts are located there. If you'd like to become a site member, simply go to the login option and it's pretty self-explanatory. Thanks to all our dedicated fans!

Church,
The Editors

For all of those few who are actually watching our progress, we have moved on. Alter-Ability lives on in all of its glory in a new form. http://alter-ability.airsoftcore.com is our new home. Feel free to check us out.

Okay, I will now type this mofo yet again since it deleted itself two seconds ago-

When season one is done, we will take everything, edit it, and post it on a new journal called like "completed seasons" or some crap like that. Then, we will take everything from this site that im posting on now "alter-ability" and delete it. Therefore this site will become the workspace for season two once we actually get to season two. Season one will be finalized in the other journal.

Now, season one, though finalized, can still be updated whenever anyone would like. That way we can go back and add all those parts that we never got a chance to. Also, this will give people a chance to add more to their characers or look over some stuff and make the first season make more sense or forshadow some stuff for the second season...

So, that's the short version...I'll explain better later, just a heads-up...skanks...

Church

Hey everyone, it's Frost/Church (Red Vs. Blue...by the way, Jack is now Caboose, Tommy is Snake/Tucker, and Tom is Grif. Anyway...)

Well, just a note on like the 20 pages or whatever that follow this- to catch everyone up really quick, there's a part about me going to Caitlin's house and being all like "Oh it's okay, I would never hurt you," bla bla bla, I love you, and so forth, but that part has been A-lost, 2-Stolen, III-Eaten, or Next-A jar of almonds. So yeah, that's very important for me to look like a badass, but at the same time profess my love to my wonderful not-evil-like-me girlfriend. THat's for all you skanks that keep making me look like an evil asshole. Which, by all means I want you to, but unbenownst to all of you, except Caitlin, I have visited her many a time before this part that I have added and come on peaceful terms...you wouldn't know because that damn part (that I've written 3 times now) is once again...misplaced. So that's so everyone understands a little about where I'm coming from- see the way that this part ends really depicts Caitlin seeing all hope is now lost...for good...sort of...

Anyway, I feel like I'm doing like audio commentary on my own movie or something, so I'll shut up, but that's just so everyone knows that there is a part that will one day be added in that explains what I just said, when I write it for the millionth time. So, I hope that clears a bit up.

Umm...well, I don't really know what else to say, but hopefully everyone enjoys this huge part and don't worry, the ending is nearly complete and a few other suprises are in store before during and after what everyone thinks is the ending...including the editors...sorry guys...don't hurt me...always like to keep my audience on the edge of their seat...

So yeah, me being the horrible person that I am have already done something to my character in the part you are about to read that's very unexpected, and made the editors "love me" and by that I mean "hate me with a flaming passion". But they, and you who is reading this, for that matter, don't know that I have at least three more suprises coming, not including two I just thought of in the last ten minutes and I'm still working out in my head as I type this. Aren't I great to my editor friends? 

So yeah, oh and there's one more suprise that only one person knows about and that one person barely knows any of it and is sworn to secrecy. YOU HEAR THAT FELLOW EDITORS? "SWORN TO SECRECY!" Yeah, so don't try and find out who, don't try to get it out of them, k? :)

Okay, now that I've made you all mad with this little piece, I'll go now...sorry...here, this will cheer you up- a whole line of smileys...

:):):):):):):):):):):):):):):):):):):):):):):):):):):):):):):):):):):):):):):):):):):):):):):):):):):)

Be happy...DON'T KILL YOUR FRIENDS...ESPECIALLY ME...HAVE A NICE DAY...
Okay, fine, here- a koala- @(*^*)@ -THere, now you can't do anything- come on, he's too cute!
And a rose for Kitty- @---}---}--- HAHAHAHAHAHA!!!...I WIN...

okay, I'm sending this for the second time to see if it reaches the post, for those that don't know, "seifercampaign" and "seifercampaign2" are both up and running. The first is the actual writing site and the second is the technical site where you can put in your history about your races, your fleet classifications, and see the stuff I've already put up.

Remember, you can do ANYTHING on Seifer Campaign, so rather than waiting for the editors to post like alter-ability, just get on and have at it. Create your own race and characters, join someone elses, and use any element of fantasy or sci-fi you want! So even though the first part is about Mark Callio, my character, you can add on something about joe shmo and what's going on over on the smuggler's planet. Make up whatever you want or use what's already there, u'll get the hang of it. 

So give seifer a try and save earth or destroy it, your choice, but there really isn't a destinctive, planned out plot like there is in alter-ability, so, try it out!

yello, folks, Frost here...

You may be asking yourself, "why is this damn thing going so slow? And why does it seem like Aaron and Tom and the other 'elected editors' are sitting on their lazy butts not doing anything?" Well, rest assured, in this little segment, I shall answer that...

First off, Tom is working hardre than humanly possible on many escapades that I keep giving him, so thank you Tom, everyone repeat after me, "Thank you Tom" he truly is a great friend for keeping up on this as much as he can, but anyway, 12 and I are currently putting in our final steps on the long awaited Seifer Campaign- yes, we hope to finally launch almost four years of work in the next two weeks and really get the ball rolling, so things are tight and life sucks as far as time goes- I'm actually losing sleep over this damn thing, and if you know me well enough, I don't get nearly enough sleep as it is.

Anyway, so Tommy needs to start writing more, which I told him and he agrees and we've brought Kai in as a possible editor so things should start picking up again. It might not seem like a lot, but believe me, there is a three-inch thick stack of papers that need to be typed for Seifer and it's not fun. 

So as soon as that gets launched, I can sit back and start updating both regularly. And then let the fun begin! Carl has also got his comp up and running and hopes to join in soon and start editing once seifer is up. 

So in summarizing, bare with us, folks, once both stories are up, things will be cool. And don't forget to check the technical accompanying live journals to understand exactly what's going on in the story in the minor details- you can learn a lot quick and understand the species, weapons, whatever, especially for seifer campaign when it comes out.

Also, if anyone would like to write the history of where their character came from and how they got their powers, let me or Tom know- all that can be added to the technical site since that's originally what we made it for.

Well, hope to be on schedule and updating soon!

Frost

Alright, everybody! This is Aaron letting all of you know that we have a ton of updates coming within the next few days hopefully. The reason progress ground to a hault is because I lost the next update from Tommy and I'm in the process of re-writing it so I can tie everything together. 

As you may or may not know, Tom is away in Las Vegas (yes, lots of jealousy or however you spell it) so he can't get to the internet that easily anymore. No fear, I've freed up a lot of time so that I can get back to editing stuff and as I told you in the previous paragraph, once Tommy's part is put in, there are literally about five parts to be added right in after that. There's also an entire history of our mythical creatures- vamps, lykoi, angels, and the such that's going to be added onto the technical site soon.

Also, be ready to join our second story which we haven't named yet, but it goes under the "SEIFER CAMPAIGN" and takes place in the year 5030 or so. That one is going to be a bit different than alter-ability but it still has great promise and I'll be adding a lot to that very shortly as well. 

In the meantime, GO SEE SPIDER-MAN 2! It's awsome!!! The village is disapointing, king aurthor has cool battle scenes, but screws up the legends completely, and BOURNE SUPREMACY IS GREAT! Still have to see Dodge-Ball, and Chronicles of Riddik was pretty good too. 

Hey, everyone say hello to our new editor Carl, by the way, he's got great ideas and he's in his junior or senior year at Towson U to become a history major. He's going to help fill in while Tom's gone and hopefully keep those ideas coming. All the editors will be meeting soon to discuss where we want the first season to go and ration out our time so that another patch of nothingness doesn't happen again. There's a lot more on the way so don't give up yet and I've got a lot of people interested in joining so be ready to hear from new folks soon. I'll send an email out to everyone just incase as well and for those who I don't have addresses from, please email them to me so that all are cought up and in the loop. My email is Deaconfrost52@hotmail.com and my cell is 443-564-8562. You can reach me on either of those or sometimes the home phone- 410-592-6109, or my dad's- 410-557-0090. 

So, look forward to a lot on the way shortly!!!

-Frost
Hi everybody I hope the story is somewhat pleasing to you.
